# CivicSync AI — Frontend PRD
> **For the frontend developer on the other laptop.**
> The backend team is handling all API routes, database, and AI logic.
> Your job: build all pages and UI components that call those APIs.

---

## Tech Stack (Frontend)

| Tool | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Next.js 15 (App Router) | Framework — already scaffolded |
| TypeScript | Language |
| Tailwind CSS | Styling |
| `react-leaflet` | Map + heatmap |
| `lucide-react` | Icons |
| `react-hot-toast` | Toast notifications |
| `@supabase/supabase-js` | Auth (passkey/email) |
| Vercel AI SDK `useObject` | AI streaming hook |

Install:
```bash
npm install react-leaflet leaflet lucide-react react-hot-toast @supabase/supabase-js ai @ai-sdk/google zod
npm install -D @types/leaflet
```

---

## Folder Structure (Frontend owns these)

```
src/
├── app/
│   ├── page.tsx                  ← Landing page
│   ├── login/page.tsx            ← Login / Signup
│   ├── report/page.tsx           ← Photo upload + AI stream
│   ├── dashboard/page.tsx        ← Citizen dashboard
│   ├── map/page.tsx              ← Cluster map + heatmap
│   ├── contact/page.tsx          ← City authorities
│   ├── admin/page.tsx            ← Admin dashboard
│   └── admin/login/page.tsx      ← Admin login
├── components/
│   ├── Navbar.tsx
│   ├── PriorityBadge.tsx
│   ├── ReportCard.tsx
│   ├── StatusTimeline.tsx
│   ├── MapView.tsx
│   ├── UploadZone.tsx
│   ├── TriageStream.tsx
│   └── StatCard.tsx
└── app/globals.css               ← Global styles
```

> **Do NOT touch:** `app/api/`, `lib/`, `knowledge/`, `supabase/`

